<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09117d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09117d">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09117d"> 117(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> sacer esto</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;Roman Law&rdquo;: In the royal laws execration (<i>sacratio capitis, <mark>sacer esto</mark></i>) was a common sanction; but in the Tables it occurs only once pure and simple, and that with reference to an offence that could be committed only by a patrician,- material loss caused by a patron to his client (<i>patronus, si clienti fraudem faxsit, sacer esto</i>). <small> <cite a>&ldquo;ROMAN LAW&rdquo;</cite></a> <a name="EBRL1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRL1"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) XXIII p. 538</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
